A worldwide policing of it? Come on. You have to get nearly every country in the World to agree first. Then bully those who won't. Its the first step toward a World Dictatorship. No thanks. Better to increase funding for developing newer safer plants and then demonstrate their superior safety to other nations. Ofcourse, many nations, in the eyes of the West, shouldn't have this technology in the first place. Like India, Pakistan, Syria etc etc etc. Clearly we have to change our stance on this first. In North Korea talks are continuing with the aim of replacing older plants for new. It's a struggle but it seems to be slowly working. Thats the best approach.  <br>
