<br>
I've long believed that moving mining and heavy industry into space would go a long way toward helping us environmentally rather then make matters worse.  One of my main issues with the environmental movement at large, as you pointed out, is that they're highly resistant to utilizing space for these activities.  They seem to think the answer to environmental problems is to drive our standard of living into the ground and to wind back the clock on technology.  With space born industry we could both have a high standard of living and have a clean planet, or at least make significant progress in that direction.  Banning people from making use of the resources in space is not the answer like so many environmentalists think!  Such a policy is not only totalitarian it's just not logical.  So to make a long post short, I like a lot of the ideas on your website.  <br>
